# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

gumshoe:SingleD6Model a rpg:ResolutionModel ;
    rpg:name "Single d6 Test" ;
    rpg:description "Roll 1d6, add spent pool points, compare to Difficulty Number (usually 4). Used only for General abilities." ;
    rpg:hasLLMArtifact gumshoe:LLM_ResolutionModel .

gumshoe:LLM_ResolutionModel a rpg:LLMArtifact ;
    rpg:artifactType rpg:Descriptor ;
    rpg:artifactAppliesTo gumshoe:SingleD6Model ;
    rpg:artifactFormat "markdown" ;
    rpg:artifactLanguage "en" ;
    rpg:artifactText """# GUMSHOE Resolution
- **Investigative abilities**: No roll. Automatic success if ability rating >= 1 and player is in right place using right ability.
- **General ability tests**: Roll 1d6 + pool points spent >= Difficulty Number.
- **Default Difficulty**: 4 for most tests and contests.
- **Contests**: Alternating rolls; first to fail loses. Each participant tries to beat DN (typically 4).
- **Toll Tests**: Success assured; roll first, then decide whether to pay the gap. Base DN 6.
- **Zero Sum Contests**: All PCs roll; best (positive) or worst (negative) result triggers the outcome.
- **Continuing Challenges**: Obstacle has a total pool (8+); PCs accumulate successes across multiple tests at DN 4.
- **The GM never reveals Difficulty Numbers beforehand** (except in Zero Sum Contests where open DN is declared).
""" .

# --- Roll Definitions ---

gumshoe:SimpleTest a rpg:Roll ;
    rpg:name "Simple Test" ;
    rpg:rollExpression "1d6 + pool_spend >= Difficulty (default 4)" ;
    rpg:rollDefinedInRuleSet gumshoe:GUMSHOE_SRD ;
    rpg:usesResolutionModel gumshoe:SingleD6Model ;
    rpg:description "A test against a fixed Difficulty with no active opposition. Spend pool points to add to roll." ;
    rpg:hasLLMArtifact gumshoe:LLM_SimpleTest .

gumshoe:LLM_SimpleTest a rpg:LLMArtifact ;
    rpg:artifactType rpg:Descriptor ;
    rpg:artifactAppliesTo gumshoe:SimpleTest ;
    rpg:artifactFormat "markdown" ;
    rpg:artifactLanguage "en" ;
    rpg:artifactText """# Simple Test
Player rolls 1d6 and may spend points from the relevant General ability pool to add to the result. The total must meet or exceed the Difficulty Number set by the GM (not revealed beforehand). A failed test means you've shot your wad — no retry unless you take a new supporting action and spend MORE points than the previous attempt.

**Piggybacking**: When a group acts in concert, one leader rolls. Others pay 1 pool point each for the benefit. Each member who can't pay increases the Difficulty by 2.

**Cooperation**: Two characters — leader rolls + spends, assistant spends points but only (N-1) of those add to the roll.
""" .

gumshoe:Contest a rpg:Roll ;
    rpg:name "Contest" ;
    rpg:rollExpression "Alternating 1d6 + pool_spend >= Difficulty (usually 4); first failure loses" ;
    rpg:rollDefinedInRuleSet gumshoe:GUMSHOE_SRD ;
    rpg:usesResolutionModel gumshoe:SingleD6Model ;
    rpg:description "Two characters alternate tests. First to fail loses. Used for chases and opposed actions." ;
    rpg:hasLLMArtifact gumshoe:LLM_Contest .

gumshoe:LLM_Contest a rpg:LLMArtifact ;
    rpg:artifactType rpg:Descriptor ;
    rpg:artifactAppliesTo gumshoe:Contest ;
    rpg:artifactFormat "markdown" ;
    rpg:artifactLanguage "en" ;
    rpg:artifactText """# Contest
Each character acts in turn (lowest rating goes first; ties: NPCs before PCs). Each makes a test. First to fail loses. The GM may assign different Difficulties to reflect advantages/disadvantages. Typical Difficulty is 4 for both sides. Narrate each exchange to keep the fiction alive.
""" .

gumshoe:TollTest a rpg:Roll ;
    rpg:name "Toll Test" ;
    rpg:rollExpression "1d6 (no pre-declared spend); then decide whether to pay gap to Difficulty 6+" ;
    rpg:rollDefinedInRuleSet gumshoe:GUMSHOE_SRD ;
    rpg:usesResolutionModel gumshoe:SingleD6Model ;
    rpg:description "Success is assured if you pay the cost. Roll first, then decide whether to spend points to bridge the gap." ;
    rpg:hasLLMArtifact gumshoe:LLM_TollTest .

gumshoe:LLM_TollTest a rpg:LLMArtifact ;
    rpg:artifactType rpg:Descriptor ;
    rpg:artifactAppliesTo gumshoe:TollTest ;
    rpg:artifactFormat "markdown" ;
    rpg:artifactLanguage "en" ;
    rpg:artifactText """# Toll Test
Success is guaranteed if you're willing to pay. Base Difficulty 6 (may be higher). You roll 1d6 WITHOUT declaring a spend. After seeing the result, decide whether to spend points to bridge the gap, or accept failure. This is about cost-benefit, not pass-fail.
""" .

gumshoe:ZeroSumContest a rpg:Roll ;
    rpg:name "Zero Sum Contest" ;
    rpg:rollExpression "All PCs roll 1d6 + secret spend; best/worst result triggers outcome" ;
    rpg:rollDefinedInRuleSet gumshoe:GUMSHOE_SRD ;
    rpg:usesResolutionModel gumshoe:SingleD6Model ;
    rpg:description "Something bad or good will happen to one PC. All roll; highest (positive) or lowest (negative) takes the outcome." .

gumshoe:ContinuingChallenge a rpg:Roll ;
    rpg:name "Continuing Challenge" ;
    rpg:rollExpression "Series of tests at DN 4; successes accumulate against obstacle pool (8+)" ;
    rpg:rollDefinedInRuleSet gumshoe:GUMSHOE_SRD ;
    rpg:usesResolutionModel gumshoe:SingleD6Model ;
    rpg:description "A prolonged effort. The obstacle has a total difficulty pool. PCs accumulate successful roll+spend totals until they overcome it. Failed tests don't contribute." .

