gumshoe:LLM_InvestigativeAbilities a rpg:LLMArtifact ;
    rpg:artifactType rpg:Descriptor ;
    rpg:artifactAppliesTo gumshoe:InvestigativeAbility ;
    rpg:artifactFormat "markdown" ;
    rpg:artifactLanguage "en" ;
    rpg:artifactText """# Investigative Abilities
- **No die roll ever.** If a PC has rating 1+ in a relevant ability and is in the right scene, they get core clues automatically.
- **Spends** (1-2 pool points) yield special benefits: extra info, narrative advantages, favorable impressions.
- **Passive clues**: GM provides without prompting when obvious to a trained investigator.
- **Active clues**: Player must declare use of a specific ability.
- **Build points**: Spread widely; even 1 point is very effective. Rarely go above 3-4 in one ability.
- **Pool refreshes** only at end of each case/investigation.

## Subcategories
- **Academic**: Knowledge and research-based (History, Law, Archaeology, etc.)
- **Interpersonal**: Social interaction-based (Flattery, Intimidation, Reassurance, etc.)
- **Technical**: Practical/scientific expertise (Forensics, Photography, Locksmith, etc.)
""" .

