    rpg:artifactType rpg:Descriptor ;
    rpg:artifactAppliesTo gumshoe:InterpersonalAbility ;
    rpg:artifactFormat "markdown" ;
    rpg:artifactLanguage "en" ;
    rpg:artifactText """# Interpersonal Abilities — GM Guidance
Interpersonal abilities are typically ACTIVE: the player must choose the right ability and describe their approach. The GM should hint when a player is on the right track:
- "You get the feeling this guy will crack if you lean on him a little." (Intimidation)
- "He seems kind of smitten by you." (Flattery)
- "The squeal of a police scanner tells you you've got a wannabe cop." (Cop Talk)

When a player picks the wrong interpersonal ability, the NPC doesn't reveal the clue but the player doesn't lose points either. Guide them gently.
""" .

