gumshoe:GeneralAbility rdfs:subClassOf rpg:RuleSetAttribute ;
    rpg:name "General Ability" ;
    rpg:description "Abilities that use 1d6 tests for uncertain outcomes. Help you survive while investigating. Concentrate points for higher ratings." ;
    rpg:hasLLMArtifact gumshoe:LLM_GeneralAbilities .

gumshoe:LLM_GeneralAbilities a rpg:LLMArtifact ;
    rpg:artifactType rpg:Descriptor ;
    rpg:artifactAppliesTo gumshoe:GeneralAbility ;
    rpg:artifactFormat "markdown" ;
    rpg:artifactLanguage "en" ;
    rpg:artifactText """# General Abilities
- **Use 1d6 + pool spend vs Difficulty Number** (usually 4, never revealed beforehand).
- **Rating 0**: Cannot make tests (but can still do mundane tasks without rolling).
- **Benchmarks**: 1-3 sideline, 4-7 solid, 8+ dedicated bad-assery.
- **Cherries**: Special features unlocked at rating 8+, always available even if pool is 0.
- **Build points**: 60 points total. Concentrate among a few abilities. Second-highest must be >= half of highest.
- **Pool refresh**: Athletics, Driving, Scuffling, Shooting refresh after 24h game-world time. Others refresh at end of case.
- **Some General abilities double as Investigative** when used to gather a clue rather than overcome opposition (setting-dependent).
""" .

