    rpg:artifactFormat "markdown" ;
    rpg:artifactLanguage "en" ;
    rpg:artifactText """# Stability — Mental Damage Thresholds
- **Test**: 1d6 + spend >= 4 when encountering stressful incidents. Loss capped at worst incident per scene.
- **0 to -5 (Shaken)**: All general Difficulties +1. Investigative spends require a test (DN = absolute Stability value).
- **-6 to -11 (Mental Illness)**: Acquire a mental illness (PTSD or supernatural disorder). Permanently lose 1 Stability rating. Continue suffering Shaken effects.
- **-12 or below (Incurably Insane)**: One last crazy act, then character is retired.

## Stability Loss Table (examples)
| Incident | Loss |
|---|---|
| Attacked with intent to harm | 2 |
| Vehicle accident | 2 |
| Attacked with intent to kill | 3 |
| See supernatural creature (distance) | 3 |
| See supernatural creature (close) | 4 |
| Grisly murder/accident scene | 4 |
| Friend/loved one violently killed (learned) | 4 |
| Discover friend/loved one's corpse | 6 |
| Attacked by supernatural creature | 7 |
| See friend/loved one killed | 7 |
| Friend/loved one killed gruesomely | 8 |

## Mental Illness (supernatural trigger)
1. Delusion, 2. Homicidal Mania, 3. Megalomania, 4. Multiple Personality, 5. Paranoia, 6. Selective Amnesia.
""" .

