# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 14. CHARACTER CREATION STRUCTURE
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

gumshoe:LLM_CharacterCreation a rpg:LLMArtifact ;
    rpg:artifactType rpg:StyleGuide ;
    rpg:artifactScope gumshoe:GUMSHOE_SRD ;
    rpg:artifactFormat "markdown" ;
    rpg:artifactLanguage "en" ;
    rpg:artifactText """# GUMSHOE Character Creation Guide

## Step 1: Concept
Choose a character concept appropriate to the setting. Some settings provide Stereotypes (flavor templates), Packages (ability minimums), or Occupations (half-price abilities + special benefits).

## Step 2: Investigative Abilities
- Points vary by group size: 2 players = 80% of x, 3 = 60%, 4 = 55%, 5+ = 50% (x = total investigative abilities in game).
- GM ensures every ability is covered by at least one PC.
- Even 1 rating point means high professional competence.
- Spread widely; rarely go above 3-4 in any one ability.
- May reserve unspent points to reveal during play.

## Step 3: General Abilities
- 60 build points regardless of group size.
- Concentrate points; you want higher ratings here than in investigative.
- Start with Health 1 and Stability 1 for free.
- Second-highest rating must be >= half of highest.
- Benchmarks: 1-3 sideline, 4-7 solid, 8+ bad-assery.
- Rating 0 = cannot make tests (but can do mundane non-critical tasks).

## Drives (optional by setting)
Personal motivation keeping the character heroically and curiously engaged.

## Packages vs Occupations
- **Packages**: Set minimum ability requirements. Fast and simple.
- **Occupations**: Key abilities at half-price (2 rating per 1 build point). May include Special mechanical benefits.
""" .

