gumshoe:LLM_Hazards a rpg:LLMArtifact ;
    rpg:artifactType rpg:Descriptor ;
    rpg:artifactScope gumshoe:GUMSHOE_SRD ;
    rpg:artifactFormat "markdown" ;
    rpg:artifactLanguage "en" ;
    rpg:artifactText """# GUMSHOE Hazards

## Electricity (and similar shocks)
- **Mild**: 1 Health lost, blown back 2m.
- **Moderate**: 2 Health lost, lose next 4 actions (buy off at 3 Athletics each).
- **Extreme**: 1d6+4 damage.
- At -6 Health: cardiac arrest or brain damage.

## Fire
- **Minor** (extremity): damage modifier -2 per round.
- **Partial** (up to half body): damage modifier +0 per round.
- **Extensive** (half+ body): damage modifier +2 per round.
- Extinguish DN usually 4.

## Suffocation
- 2 minutes before effects. Then lose 1 Athletics per 10 seconds. When Athletics depleted, lose 1 Health per 5 seconds.

## Toxins
- Inhaled: immediate. Injected/ingested: delayed (minutes to hours).
- Damage modifier range: -2 (cleaning substance) to +16 (nerve gas).
- May prevent Health refresh until neutralized.

## GM Rule: Always give PCs some opportunity to avoid hazards.
""" .

