    rpg:artifactFormat "markdown" ;
    rpg:artifactLanguage "en" ;
    rpg:artifactText """# GUMSHOE Opponent Design

## Stat Block Template
- **Abilities**: Athletics N, Health N, Scuffling N, Shooting N (plus setting-specific)
- **Scuffling Weapons/Damage**: weapon type +/-modifier
- **Shooting Weapons/Damage**: weapon type +/-modifier
- **Hit Threshold**: 3 default (2 for large/slow, 4+ for agile/small/supernatural)
- **Armor**: Subtracted from each damage instance. May be weapon-specific.
- **Alertness Modifier**: Applied to Infiltration/Surveillance difficulties. Second number after slash = without gear.
- **Stealth Modifier**: Alters Surveillance difficulty to spot opponent.
- **Attack Pattern** (optional): Suggested per-round spending. Increase after misses.

## Design Principles
- **Health = dramatic endurance**, not realistic toughness. A thug who should fall to one burst = Health 1-2.
- **Most NPCs need only text description** — stats only for those who must be overcome through general abilities.
- **Always consult story logic first**, attack patterns second.
- **Player-facing**: prefer player tests over GM rolls for supporting characters.
- **False branching**: Don't roll for NPCs when players can't affect the outcome. Just decree it happens.
""" .

